author: amilas
msg: isWrapped is used with the RPCMessage receiver. Its' meaning is whether the generated elements
from an POJO wrapped with the method name or not.
if we set the wrapped here based on the wsdl is rpc/lit type or not then that may cause problems if some one
put a generated wsdl into a .aar file with the rpc message receiver.
